# Ollama governance peer review (token economics)

## When to run

After an **implementation slice** is complete and structural checks pass, before writing the canonical `*-peer-review-receipt.md`:

1. `npm run check:<slice>` (or `npm run check:quick` during edits)
2. `npm run peer-review:ollama -- --slice <profile> --dry-run`
3. `npm run peer-review:ollama -- --slice <profile> --write` (when operator key/host available)
4. Run validation commands from the draft receipt
5. Finalize canonical peer review receipt only after checks pass

## Slice profile map

| Gate | Profile id |
| --- | --- |
| RUNTIME-002B peer review | `runtime-002b` |
| RUNTIME-002A peer review | `runtime-002a` |
| Ad-hoc / new slice | `generic` + `--files` |

List all profiles: `npm run peer-review:ollama -- --list-slices`

Read `docs/ai/ollama-peer-review-runbook.md` before first use.

## Rules

- Do **not** treat `*-ollama-peer-review-draft.md` as PASS without running checks.
- Do **not** read or commit `secrets/` contents.
- Prefer Ollama draft review over re-deriving the full peer review prompt in Cursor when a profile exists.
- Cursor agent still validates, edits, and commits the **final** receipt.
- Product Ibal provider Settings use `docs/ai/provider-settings-contract.md` — not this harness.

## Forbidden

- Marking UI-003E PASS from an Ollama draft
- Skipping `npm run check` / cargo because the draft says Pass
- Pasting API keys into receipts, PR bodies, or chat
